CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 16, 1961, pg. 11 reads: "Crosses Picket Line - This unidentified shopper has casually ignored the NAACP picket line at this downtown shoe store, which does not employ Negro sales clerks. Pittsburgh residents are asked NOT to follow her example and to refrain from buying goods at Chandler's, Burt's and Baker's shoe stores on downtown Fifth Ave. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women standing outside of Baker's Shoes, street no. 310, with sign in window advertising casual shoes $3.99 - $4.99 and up
